HEADWORD: Melanosperm
<hw>Me*lan"o*sperm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`las</grk>, <grk>me`lanos</grk>, black + <grk>spe`rma</grk>
seed.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An alga of any kind that produces
blackish spores, or seed dust. The melanosperms include the rockweeds
and all kinds of kelp.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Mel`a*no*sper"mous</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melanotic</ent>⟦br⟧
